What is Linux operating system?
Linux is an general purpose operating system released in 1991 by Linus Torvalds. Linux has been build on a phylosophy where software should be distributed freely and sourcecode should be made accessible and modifiable freely, that is where Linux is distributed under GNU license

The major component of the Linux operating system is "Kernel", kernel interacts with the hardware components of the computer enabling the software programs to run/communicate with underlying hardware


Little background about Linux operating system
MINIX is the initial operating system that has been developed on an experimental grounds, inspired by the outcome of MINIX, the UNIX operating system has been build by ken Thompson from AT&T. UNIX is licensed operating system and cannot be re-distributable and the sourcecode is not be made accessible.
	
Linus Torvalds wanted to build an operating system that is opensource and even the sourcecode should be free distributable and modifiable that is where LINUX operating system has began its journey.
	
Linux operating system is defined by its "kernal", no gui


opensource contributors "GNU Project", sophisticated gui tools and utilities that can be installed ontop of the linux operating system to make that user friendly

Music Players
Graphical User Interface
